If you&#39;re really stuck with `Any?` you could use this rather unsafe way:

```kotlin
fun getFilteredItems(param: Any?): List&lt;Item&gt; = when(param) {
    &quot;ALL&quot;, null -&gt; items
    is List&lt;*&gt; -&gt; items.filter { it.id in param }
    else -&gt; error(&quot;Invalid filter parameter &#39;$param&#39;&quot;)
}
```

But that doesn&#39;t fail if the list contains other things than `Long`, it will just return an empty list in that case.

A better, more type-safe way is to type your parameter with a sealed class:

```kotlin
sealed class Filter {

    object All : Filter()

    data class ById(val ids: List&lt;Long&gt;): Filter()
}

fun getFilteredItems(param: Filter): List&lt;Item&gt; = when(param) {
    Filter.All -&gt; items
    is Filter.ById -&gt; items.filter { it.id in param.ids }
}
```

